FT  15 AUG 92 / Haiti returnees held
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PORT-AU-PRINCE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Haitian police yesterday detained more than 150 boat people minutes after
the US Coast Guard forcibly returned them to their homeland, AP reports from
Port-au-Prince. A police officer said they would be questioned about the
hijacking of the 40-ft vessel in which they made their escape.
</TEXT>
