Her Majesty's health. Eight years on and the same loyal politician, Harry
Rimmer, is leader of the Liverpool council, and will be on duty this weekend
when Spain's King Juan Carlos presents prizes to the crews of the 76 ships
celebrating Columbus's voyage to the New World 500 years ago. Earlier this
week Rimmer persuaded tenants of 67 council tower blocks to join a
government-sponsored housing action trust. If Rimmer keeps on like this, he
should be in line for the customary knighthood.
