FT  14 AUG 92 / Australian GDP grows by 0.6%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMILIA TAGAZA
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CANBERRA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Australia's gross domestic product grew by a modest 0.6 per cent in the
three months ending June, confirming that national recovery from recession
would be a long slow haul, writes Emilia Tagaza from Canberra. The rise was
the largest since recovery began a year ago and brought the 1990-91 annual
growth rate to 1.6 per cent. After release of the national account figures
yesterday, the currency regained some lost ground. But analysts said the
markets would stay edgy until the projected budget deficit size is known
next week. Forecasts put it near ADollars 14bn (Pounds 5.4bn).
