FT  14 AUG 92 / UN to place troops in Somalia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL LITTLEJOHNS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   UNITED NATIONS, NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The United Nations, moving swiftly to follow up a breakthrough agreement
with Somalia's warlords, proposed last night to send in 500 Pakistani troops
to ensure the safe delivery of food and other aid to millions of starving
people in Somalia, Michael Littlejohns reports from the United Nations in
New York.
Mr Boutros Boutros Ghali, UN secretary-general, formally notified the
Security Council about the plan and officials said its assent seemed
routine.
The accord with the Somali leaders calls for the deployment of UN soldiers
within 21 days but Mr Kofi Annan, UN official in charge, said it was hoped
the Pakistanis could arrive in the country within a fortnight. Deploying
them, though, might take 'several weeks'.
