<HEADLINE>
FT  14 AUG 92 / Portugal lifts curb on capital movements
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PORTUGAL is to lift restrictions on capital movements imposed last year to
prevent investment from overseas upsetting the country's monetary targets.
The Bank of Portugal said that all remaining restrictions would be lifted in
three phases by the end of the year.
The first phase will come on August 31, when Portuguese borrowers in foreign
currency will be excused the obligation to deposit 25 per cent of the money
in interest-free accounts with the central bank.
Foreigners will be allowed full access to the Portuguese money markets from
December 31.
</TEXT>
