reports from Boston.
The bank which raised Dollars 223m in net proceeds from the offering, said
the underwriting group, led by Merrill Lynch, exercised their right to
purchase the maximum over-allotment of 1.2m shares.
The offering would raise the bank's capital ratios by about 0.75 per cent,
bringing the pro forma Tier I and total capital ratios to 6.7 and 11 per
cent respectively, the bank said.
