Stripping out this gain, pre-tax profits for the period showed a near-40 per
cent increase. After a tax charge of Pounds 200,000 (Pounds 204,000 credit)
net profits came out at Dollars 13.3m (Dollars 16.1m). Fully diluted
earnings per share emerged at 80 cents (Dollars 1.31 adjusted for scrip
issue).
This brings pre-tax profits for the half year to end-June to Dollars 4.75m
(Dollars 5.34m) on revenue ahead to Dollars 193.8m (Dollars 172.8m).
