agreement. 'The Commission always welcomes free trade areas, on condition
they respect Gatt rules'.
The EC states have agreed to form an ambitious European free trade zone
(European Economic Area) with the European Free Trade Agreement (Efta). An
EC official said Nafta would offer attractions to outside investors. 'We
can't do anything about that. That's what markets are about'. The EC is
likely to study Nafta's car, textile and financial services clauses.
