<HEADLINE>
FT  13 AUG 92 / Italian rail given change of status
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ITALY'S Economic Planning Committee yesterday approved the transformation of
the national rail system into a joint stock company, AP reports from Rome.
The shares of Ente Ferrovia dello Stato (FS), which will be Italy's largest
joint stock company with capital of L42 trillion (million million) - Pounds
19.6bn - will belong to the Treasury Ministry and stakes will eventually be
transferred to the Transport and Budget ministries as well.
The government hopes to raise about L42 trillion from privatisations by 1995
to reduce the budget deficit. The move follows transformation last week of
the country's four main holding companies into joint stock companies to
prepare for privatisation.
</TEXT>
