support was plotted at Pounds 610 for the December contract. 'It's not cocoa
that is weighing on the market, but speculators. The problem is there's been
no decent buying around. A lot of bulls are happy to see the market come
down so they can buy on the dips," another dealer said. London's robusta
COFFEE prices also dropped back after New York scored new life-of-contract
lows, weighed down by the abundance of supply. Trading remained dull on the
LME as the summer slowdown in physical interest and an absence of fresh news
continued to restrict activity, dealers said. Prices closed mixed, although
COPPER and ZINC slipped through the floors of their current trading ranges,
while ALUMINIUM was near its downside support, they said.
