provisional liquidation earlier this month.
Walbrook was a significant creditor of Weavers, and provided it with limited
financial support. Its winding up made it impossible for Weavers to continue
operating.
Mr Hocking said he expected to present a full report on the history of the
company and its financial position to a meeting of creditors on August 24.
He said it was inevitable that litigation would ensue between Weavers and
Walbrook, other LUI subsidiaries and third parties, including other
creditors.
