<TEXT>
NCM CREDIT Insurance, the Dutch company that paid Pounds 70m for the Export
Credits Guarantee Department's short-term business last December, is to
locate its headquarters in Cardiff's docklands development.
It will lease a 115,000 sq ft building being erected by Grosvenor Waterside,
property arm of Associated British Ports.
As a result of the sale, NCM has had to move out of Crown premises in
