NCM's decision means Grosvenor Waterside has attracted two large concerns to
its 160-acre development within Cardiff Bay. Last year, the Welsh Health
Common Services Authority, a public-sector body, announced that it would
take an office block nearby.
The NCM decision is a boost for the Cardiff Bay project, set up five years
ago to redevelop 2,700 acres of Cardiff's docklands.
